    "body": "## Summary\nThis PR adds Docker-based test evaluation infrastructure for Bitcoin Core using the Helix framework.\n\n## Changes\n- **`.helix/Dockerfile.helix`**: Multi-stage Docker configuration\n  - Uses Ubuntu 24.04 base image (matches CI environment)\n  - Installs all required build dependencies (cmake, boost, libevent, etc.)\n  - Configures ccache for compilation caching\n  - Builds Bitcoin Core with wallet, ZMQ, and IPC support\n  - Optimized for test execution\n\n- **`.helix/run-tests-eval.sh`**: Test execution script\n  - Configurable parallel job execution (default: 4 jobs)\n  - Support for extended tests and fail-fast mode\n  - Color-coded output for easy status identification\n  - Verifies build artifacts before test execution\n\n## Test Suite Coverage\n- 300+ Python functional tests via `test/functional/test_runner.py`\n- Supports standard and extended test suites\n- Parallel execution for faster results\n\n## Resource Requirements\n- **Minimum**: 2GB RAM, 4GB disk, 2 CPU cores\n- **Recommended**: 4GB RAM, 8GB disk, 4+ CPU cores\n\n## Build Times\n- Fresh build: 30-60 minutes\n- With ccache: 5-15 minutes\n- Test execution: 20-40 minutes (60-90 minutes for extended)\n\n## Verification\nThe Docker configuration follows Bitcoin Core's CI/CD best practices and uses the same Ubuntu 24.04 base image as the official GitHub Actions workflows.",
